# HTML Best Practices

## Critical Rules

- Document Structure
  - Use proper HTML5 doctype and language declaration
  - Include meta tags for charset and viewport
  - Organize head section with proper meta tags and title
  - Use semantic HTML elements (nav, main, article, etc.)
  - Maintain logical document outline

- Accessibility (a11y)
  - Add ARIA labels and roles where appropriate
  - Ensure proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
  - Provide alt text for images
  - Maintain keyboard navigation support
  - Use semantic elements for better screen reader support

- Forms and Input
  - Label all form controls properly
  - Group related form elements with fieldset
  - Use appropriate input types (email, tel, number, etc.)
  - Implement proper form validation attributes
  - Add helpful error messages and aria-invalid states

- Performance and SEO
  - Minimize inline styles and scripts
  - Use async/defer for script loading
  - Implement proper meta tags for SEO
  - Optimize image loading with srcset and sizes
  - Follow proper link structure for SEO

- Maintainability
  - Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
  - Add comments for complex structures
  - Keep markup clean and minimal
  - Use meaningful class and ID names
  - Maintain consistent naming conventions

## Examples

<example>
  <!-- Good - Proper document structure with semantic elements -->
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Inventory Management - Item Details</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Manage your game inventory items">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <header role="banner">
      <nav role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/" aria-current="page">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="/inventory">Inventory</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main role="main">
      <h1>Item Details</h1>
      
      <!-- Good - Accessible form structure -->
      <form action="/inventory/update" method="POST" novalidate>
        <fieldset>
          <legend>Item Information</legend>
          
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="item-name">Item Name</label>
            <input 
              type="text" 
              id="item-name" 
              name="itemName" 
              required 
              aria-required="true"
              aria-describedby="name-help"
            >
            <small id="name-help">Enter the full item name</small>
          </div>

          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="item-quantity">Quantity</label>
            <input 
              type="number" 
              id="item-quantity" 
              name="quantity" 
              min="0" 
              max="99"
              required
            >
          </div>
        </fieldset>

        <button type="submit" aria-label="Save item details">Save</button>
      </form>
    </main>

    <footer role="contentinfo">
      <p>&copy; 2024 Game Inventory</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
  </html>
</example>

<example type="invalid">
  <!-- Bad - Poor structure and accessibility -->
